cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.CE 

The paper discusses Non-Intrusive Load Monitoring (NILM) which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence applied to energy consumption data. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the evaluation of NILM approaches, which involves signal processing and system identification techniques, making cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper discusses the application of NILM to energy-efficient buildings, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CE (Computing and Engineering).
